  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow">Guide</p>
    <h1>PDF to Excel vs PDF Table Extraction</h1>
    <p>PDF to Excel conversion and PDF table extraction sound similar, but they solve different jobs.</p>
    <h2>PDF to Excel conversion</h2>
    <p>This approach tries to recreate the entire document in a spreadsheet. It can be useful for forms, invoices, and layout-heavy files, but it may create messy sheets.</p>
    <h2>PDF table extraction</h2>
    <p>This approach ignores most page layout and focuses on detected table rows and columns. It is better when your goal is analysis, sorting, filtering, or charting.</p>
    <h2>Which should you choose?</h2>
    <p>Choose table extraction when the data matters more than visual fidelity. Choose full conversion when preserving the page layout is the priority.</p>
